As simple and bland as it sounds, this is a great side dish. The flavor is simple yet rounded, and goes really well with steak (I cooked it with "Marinated Filet of Beef). The texture of the carrots is similar to potato and so it is easy to leave starch out of the meal. As always, I increased the garlic by a clove or two.

